<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-02-01T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-02-01T10:00:00-05:00" n="504" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d504">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">701.6260D/18: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Finland</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Gullion</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Helsinki</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-02-01T17:00:00+02:00">February 1, 1944—5 p.m.</date>
                                    <lb/> [Received February 1—2:27 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>78. I am informed by a reliable diplomatic source that Blucher,
                                German Minister, has been called to confer with Hitler at his
                                headquarters. <pb facs="0573" n="561" xml:id="pg_561"/> Blücher left
                                here yesterday or the day before accompanied by Metzger, German
                                Press Attaché. I have not yet heard any explanation of this
                                visit.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Gullion</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>